==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''prae'' "before", and ''supponere'' "to [[suppose]]".

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-əʊz|-əʊz]]

===Verb===
'''presuppose'''
# To assume some truth without proof, usually for the purpose of reaching a conclusion based on that truth.

